                <h3>How are stars created?</h3>
                Stars are formed from dust clouds in the middle of space.<br>
                These clouds of dust can form masses big enough that they are pulled together by gravity.<br>
                Material at the center of the cloud becomes hotter and eventually creates a protostar, eventually this protostar will become a full star.[<a href="https://science.nasa.gov/astrophysics/focus-areas/how-do-stars-form-and-evolve">REF</a>]<br>

            </div>


            <div>
                <h3>How many stars can we see from Earth</h3>
                The number of stars that could be visible from earth is around 10,000.<br>
                This number is closer to 5,000 possibly visible at one time due to only half of the Earth being at nightime at any given moment.<br>
                You may see more or less depending on things like the strength of your eyesight, the amount of light in the area around you, and the condition of the sky.[<a href="https://earthsky.org/astronomy-essentials/how-many-stars-could-you-see-on-a-clear-moonless-night">REF</a>]<br>
            </div>
        </div>


